Note:
Linux ARM32 (ARMv7) Instruction Set Metadata and Helpers

This file provides instruction metadata, opcode identifiers, and helper functions
for ARM32 instruction selection, validation, and optimization on Linux.

ARM32 (ARMv7-A) Key Characteristics:
- Fixed 32-bit (4-byte) ARM instruction length, or 16/32-bit Thumb-2
- Load/store architecture (memory access only via LDR/STR variants)
- Conditional execution on (almost) every instruction via 4-bit condition codes
- 3-operand instructions (dest can differ from sources)
- Flexible second operand: register with optional shift, or rotated 8-bit immediate
- CPSR condition flags: N, Z, C, V set by S-suffixed variants
- PC-relative addressing with 12-bit signed offset for load/store literals
- Branches: B/BL (24-bit offset shifted left 2), BX/BLX for interworking

ARMv7 extensions used by ARM32 Linux code generation:
- VFPv3/VFPv4: Single and double precision floating point (S0-S31, D0-D31)
- NEON (Advanced SIMD): 128-bit vector operations (Q0-Q15 or D0-D31)
- Integer divide (SDIV/UDIV) in ARMv7-VE; falls back to helper call elsewhere

Encoding identifiers vs. actual binary encodings:
This file assigns logical identifiers (small integers) to each instruction
mnemonic. These identifiers drive instruction selection and scheduling
decisions. The actual ARM binary encoding happens in machine_code.runa.

Dependencies:
- registers.runa for register metadata and encoding indices
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/platform/linux_arm32/registers.runa" as Registers

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONDITION CODE CONSTANTS (ARMv7 4-bit cond field)
Note: ============================================================================

Note:
ARM conditional execution uses a 4-bit field appended to almost every
instruction. A condition of AL (always) is the common default. These values
match the architectural encoding (ARMv7 ARM A8.3).
:End Note

Constant COND_EQ as Integer is 0
Constant COND_NE as Integer is 1
Constant COND_CS as Integer is 2
Constant COND_CC as Integer is 3
Constant COND_MI as Integer is 4
Constant COND_PL as Integer is 5
Constant COND_VS as Integer is 6
Constant COND_VC as Integer is 7
